---
# .ansible-lint — lint policy for this repo.
#
# A full run found no actual defects: every waiver below is a deliberate,
# documented convention of this codebase, so the linter is matched to it rather
# than reformatting intentional code. Genuine issues are still fixed in code
# (and rules that catch real risks, e.g. risky-file-permissions, stay active —
# the one intentional exception carries an inline `# noqa`).
#
# Note: run with community.general resolvable (a full Ansible install, or
# ANSIBLE_COLLECTIONS_PATH pointed at it), or homebrew_cask / git_config /
# ini_file cannot be loaded for options validation.

skip_list:
  # Loop tasks carry a leading per-item label, e.g. "[{{ entry.tool }}] Wire …",
  # so run output identifies the item. name[template] wants templates only at
  # the end of a name.
  - name[template]

  # Git is driven through the git CLI on purpose: the repo's stance is
  # non-destructive git (fetch / status / rev-parse, never reset --hard or
  # force), which ansible.builtin.git cannot express safely. See AGENTS.md.
  - command-instead-of-module

  # `command -v <tool>` detection uses a shell builtin, so the shell module is
  # required, not command; command-instead-of-shell misreads this as needless.
  - command-instead-of-shell

  # A couple of loop inputs align dict values into columns with extra spaces
  # after a comma, for readability; yaml[commas] permits only one.
  - yaml[commas]
...
